KANO – Kano State Government has approved the promotion of 152 staff in the mainstream of the civil service for the month of February 2022. The Chairman Civil Service Commission, Engineer Bello Mohammad Kiru, announced this at the routine commission exercise meeting for senior staff promotion exercise held at the conference hall of the commission. The Chairman explained that 66 number of those promoted are between grade level 08 – 09, 35 are from grade level 10 to above while one person from grade level 15 to 16 is aspiring for a Directorship respectively. PDP Holds NEC Meeting On Tuesday Troops Neutralise Scores Of Terrorists Across States Engr Kiru maintained that promotion is a privilege, therefore, charged those opportune to be promoted at this crucial moment to be more alive and innovative to their duties, since there is more expectation on them. Earlier, in his remark, the Permanent Secretary of the commission, Alhaji Sani Abdullahi Kofar Mata, represented by the Director Administration Salahuddeen Habib Isa dwelt on the performance of the commission members and enjoined them to observed ethics of the civil service rules for effective and efficient service delivery.